Context:
The College Application Information Session is designed for domestic applicants (Canadian citizens or permanent residents) to guide them through the application process for full-time programs at George Brown College. The duration of the session is approximately 1 hour and it's free of cost. Interested individuals can check availability and register on the website. Attending this session is not a requirement to apply to the college, but attendees will receive updates about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more by signing up.

The contact information for inquiries is 416-415-2000 with TTY: 1-877-515-5559 and the email address ask.george@georgebrown.ca. More information about the college's land acknowledgment can also be found on the website. Please note that this session is for domestic students, international applicants should refer to the international application guide.

Phone Number: 416-415-2000, 1-877-515-5559
Email Address: ask.george@georgebrown.ca
Type of Students: Domestic (Canadian citizens or permanent residents)
Duration: Approximately 1 hour
Cost: Free
Registration and Information: Check availability and Register!
Website: Visit Our Social Media Hub
Note: Attending this session is not required to apply to George Brown College.
